init_text:
What Stereotypical Characters Make You Cringe?

What stereotypical characters in books, movies or television shows make you cringe and why? Would you ever not watch or read something because of its offensive portrayal of someone?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is the 1950s and 1960s, not today.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: but that's not the case anymore.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There should not be this stigma where women can't do anything except care for the home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I definitely would not watch or read something that reduces the status of women.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Women in this day and age have so much potential.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think this is a stereotype that could cause some damage if it is not removed soon, especially if these shows are watched by young and impressionable girls

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We need to show young kids that women can do whatever they want, and that they can be whatever the equivalent of a man is.
